

Ch2 Motion in ID


    Velocity: Measures change in position over time (vector v->) m/sec
    Speed: Magnitutde of velocity vector
    Acceleration: Measures the rate of change in velocity over time (m/sec)/sec^2
    Motion: change in position over time



    Example of Motion

           t(sec)    | x(t) (m)
        ----------------------------
             0       |      4
             1       |      5
             2       |      10
             3       |      8
             4       |      -3
             5       |      -2                  x-> (1)
             6       |      1                   |-------------->
                                    . .. .. .. .. .. .. .. .. .. .. .. .. .. .. .. .. ..
                                    ----------------------------------------------------
                                                              t=1        t=3       t=2

                                                Display motion in positon vs. time graph [x(t) vs t graph]


